{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38742c09-4734-4fc7-99cc-48bd4156be04","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — MSTest.Sdk gives you the simplest possible config:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — no `<PackageReference>` items needed. The SDK brings in MSTest, the runner, and code analyzers automatically.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution** — add a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>           <!-- 0 = one worker per core -->\n      <Scope>ClassLevel</Scope>      <!-- classes run in parallel -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nThen reference it in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run database tests sequentially** — use `[DoNotParallelize]` on those classes:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]  // ← runs sequentially, after all parallel tests finish\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void CanInsertRecord() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void CanQueryRecords() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`[DoNotParallelize]`** on a class pulls it out of the parallel pool entirely — those tests run one-at-a-time *after* all parallel tests complete.\n- **`Scope=ClassLevel`** means different classes run in parallel but methods within a class are sequential — safest default for shared per-class fixtures.\n- **`Workers=0`** auto-scales to your CPU core count. Set a specific number if your CI has resource constraints.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92eaa414-520b-4a26-ad03-b11f7fb6c3f7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant plugins or project files. Let me provide the recommended MSTest setup based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":578,"requestId":"5818:2BCA1C:5C05CDE:63F1F1C:6A033949"},"id":"ae40df1d-602e-49a4-9797-4924289231a1","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:29:41.987Z","parentId":"c4695ac3-6ede-4f28-b516-34c48339184c"}
